FBIS4-67695 "jptep009___94054" JPRS-TEP-94-009 JPRS Epidemiology 25 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA CUBA Official Comments on Use of Vitamin Supplement After Official Comments on Use of Vitamin Supplement After Neuropathy Epidemic FL2503173094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 GMT 25 Mar 94 FL2503173094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Spanish BFN [Excerpt] Several months after the neuropathy epidemic, only 37 percent of the population in Pinar del Rio takes the Neo-Vitaminic 2 vitamin supplement that is given to the population for free. This was determined through a survey carried out by the center of sociopolitical studies of the provincial committee of the Communist Party of Cuba in Pinar del Rio. The survey showed 40 percent do not use the supplement regularly, nine percent believe they do not need the supplement, eight percent took the supplement only for a few months, and three percent take other vitamins they consider more effective.[passage omitted]
